label: Main drinking water source
codebookDescription: What is the main source of drinking water for members of the household?
codebookValues:
1 = Piped into dwelling
2 = Piped to yard/plot
3 = Public tap/stand pipe
4 = Tube well or borehole
5 = Protected well
6 = Unprotected well
7 = Surface water (river/dam/ lake/pond/stream/canal/ irrigation canal)
8 = Other

label: Time to water source < 10 mins
codebookDescription: Do they have to walk more than 10 minutes to get to the primary water source?

label: Drinking water treatment
codebookDescription: Do they treat their water in any way to make it safer to drink?  If no, proceed to question 17.

label: Water treatment materials
codebookDescription: What does the family usually   do to the water to make it safer to   drink?
codebookValues:
1 = Let it stand and settle
2 = Solar disinfection
3 = Use water filter (ceramic /sand/ composite/etc.)
4 = Strain through a cloth
5 = Add bleach/chlorine
6 = Boil
7 =  Other

label: Latrine type
codebookDescription: What kind of toilet facility do members of the family usually use?
codebookValues:
1 = No facility/bush/field or bucket toilet
2 = Pit latrine without concrete slab
3 = Pit latrine with concrete slab
4 = Flush toilet
5 = Other

label: Sanitation score
definition: Whether the household sanitation facilities were classified as improved or unimproved, based on WHO definitions; 0 for unimproved categories, 4 for improved categories
codebookDescription: Score of sanitation; 0 for unimproved categories, 4 for improved categories
codebookValues:
if cef_toilet = 1 then newsanitation=0, unimproved
if cef_toilet = 2,3,4,5,6,7 then newsanitation=4, improved

label: Drinking water score
definition: Whether the household drinking water source was categorized as improved or unimproved, based on WHO definitions.; 0  for unimproved categories, 4 for improved categories
codebookDescription: Score of drinking water source; 0  for unimproved categories, 4 for improved categories
codebookValues:
if cef_main_src_drinking = 1,2,3,4,5,8 then newdrink=4,
if cef_main_src_drinking = 6,7 then newdrink=0 "unimproved"

label: Household wealth index, numerical
definition:
Sum of 8 assets scores. Household has: mattress,chair,table,tv,refrigertaor,bank account,kitchen, 
< 2 people per room. Positive reponses for each of these get a score of 1 while negative responses get 0.

label: WAMI index
definition:
The wami index is calculated by summing values of the following variables:
water, med.wami,
asset, 
incat (income), 
and dividing the total by 32

label: Protocol passed
definition:
All pids in mITT who met the following:a. Breastfed (at least partially) through age 6 months
b. Received all doses of azithromycin
c. Received initial dose of each nitazoxanide course
d. Received no more than one drug administration (at 6, 9, 12, and 15 month visits) outside of the 14-day window around the target date
e. Received at least 50% of nicotinamide doses as measured by pill and sachet counting
codebookDescription:
